A cheeky Glaswegian has taken on a household supplies firm after they used an actor in their advert who looked just like himJoker Paul Kelly from Bearsden contacted German firm Karcher via Facebook in a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Post" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Post" target="_blank">post</a> to pull them up for &quotunjust exploitation&quot of his face in an advert for their power washerHe then demanded that the firm compensate him with a lifetime supply of Irn Bru a sixfigure sum of hard cash Sterling a spot in their next advert as the evil twin or a free pressure washerThe HGV driver said &quotOne of the guy's at work said the guy in advert looked like me So I found it on YouTube and I could see the resemblanceEven my mum and dad were startled by just how much I looked like him &quotI like to think I have a good sense of humour so I thought I would <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Post" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Post" target="_blank">post</a> this to their page&quotSurprisingly however the firm took Paul's case on board and opened up Facegate to their Facebook fansGerry Hayes said &quotSeems legit&quotPaul Hirst added &quotNice to see a bit of friendly humour on Facebook he deserves a washer for his cheek&quotAnd it seems Karcher agreed with Paul who now has a new pressure washer on his way to himPaul added &quotI have been crying with laughter over this We have a Karcher in the garage but this is top of the range so I am happy I was only doing it for a laugh&quotI have to admit though I have never been so popular on Facebook&quot
